1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:03,928
A useful code captures what a passage means in relation

2
00:00:03,928 --> 00:00:05,468
to the research question.

3
00:00:05,468 --> 00:00:09,316
It should be specific enough to guide future decisions and

4
00:00:09,316 --> 00:00:11,240
broad enough to recognise again.

5
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:14,287
Open Code to create a code deliberately.

6
00:00:14,287 --> 00:00:18,069
Give it a short name, write a definition that distinguishes

7
00:00:18,069 --> 00:00:21,851
it from nearby concepts and use colour as a visual

8
00:00:21,851 --> 00:00:24,120
aid, not as the meaning itself.

9
00:00:24,520 --> 00:00:28,484
Select the smallest passage that still carries the intended meaning.

10
00:00:28,484 --> 00:00:32,448
Check the sentences around it, then apply an existing code

11
00:00:32,448 --> 00:00:36,412
or create a new one when the concept is genuinely

12
00:00:36,412 --> 00:00:36,808
different.

13
00:00:37,208 --> 00:00:39,078
Open the codebook regularly.

14
00:00:39,078 --> 00:00:43,755
Codes with similar definitions may need merging; codes with very

15
00:00:43,755 --> 00:00:46,093
different examples may need splitting.

16
00:00:46,093 --> 00:00:51,704
Counts are prompts for review, not proof that a theme is important.

17
00:00:52,104 --> 00:00:55,952
When the canvas becomes familiar, use the command palette to

18
00:00:55,952 --> 00:00:58,646
reach common actions without hunting through menus.

19
00:00:58,646 --> 00:01:02,494
Search by the outcome you want and keep your attention

20
00:01:02,494 --> 00:01:03,648
on the material.

21
00:01:04,048 --> 00:01:08,815
As coding continues, connections accumulate between sources and concepts.

22
00:01:08,815 --> 00:01:14,113
Use that visual structure to notice repetition, contradiction and gaps,

23
00:01:14,113 --> 00:01:18,880
then return to the transcript before drawing a conclusion.

24
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:21,113
Coding is iterative.

25
00:01:21,113 --> 00:01:26,611
Apply a code, compare examples and refine the definition.

26
00:01:26,611 --> 00:01:32,720
QualCanvas keeps those decisions visible, but the interpretation remains yours.
